rComments: She is a really good lecturer who explains things clearly in lectures, and is really helpful to students as well. First year in a pandemic is tough but her lectures are interesting and I am enjoying this course!

She's really clear about her expectations for grading and assignments and gives a little bit of extra credit through Echo360. If you participate through Echo360 she'll bump your grade up if possible. I rarely attended entire lectures but I got a B+ on the exam from just going through the textbook and lecture slides.

I really don't recommend! it was my biggest mistake since I took it as an elective. there's an insane amount of readings and exams are hard. Avoid her but if she's your only choice just be ready to study your life away.

She uses cool content in lecture to help you understand key ideas. Really open to questions and encourages us to get involved. Also super caring if you need help and go to speak to her. Tests are good if you went to class and did reading no surprises.
Very boring lectures, all of the material is directly out of the textbook which makes you really not want to show up. Her midterms are much harder compared to my other courses.

Definitely new to being a prof. Lectures are very boring & uninteresting. First mandatory class in my major and rly disliked it. Should probably read the textbooks on top of her lectures because she doesnt really say much & then makes the midterm very difficult.

I dont know how I feel about her, she seems like a nice lady, but the lecture content is quite heavy. The midterm so far is much more difficult than any other courses I've taken so far. Gordon is a much better crim professor.

Dr. Bracken-Roche is a great prof. I have enjoyed all of her classes, because the material is interesting and she makes it fun. Always available for discussion, very relaxed lecture atmosphere to encourage students! Exam was a little tough but fair if you did relevant reading.
